  "What is the 'polar form' of a complex number?": "复数的“ 极化形式” 是什么 ?",
  "The polar form r(cos θ + i sin θ) expresses a complex number using its distance from the origin (modulus r) and the angle it makes with the positive real axis (argument θ).": "极形 r(cos + + i sin ) 表示一个复杂数, 使用它与源(modulus r) 的距离和它与正真实轴(参数 + ) 的角。",
  "What is the 'modulus' of a complex number?": "复杂数字的“ 模量” 是什么?",
  "The modulus (or absolute value) of a + bi is |a + bi| = √(a² + b²). It represents the distance from the origin to the point (a, b) in the complex plane.": "+ 双的模量(或绝对值)是 a + bi = (a2 + b2),代表复合平面从来源到点(a,b)的距离。",
  "What is the 'argument' of a complex number?": "复杂数字的“参数”是什么?",
  "The argument (arg) is the angle θ from the positive real axis to the line connecting the origin and the complex number. It is found using θ = tan⁻¹(b/a), adjusted for quadrant.": "参数( arg) 是正实际轴到连接源和复合号的线的角度 。 它使用  = tan-1( b/ a) 并按象限调整后发现 。",
  "What is 'De Moivre's Theorem'?": "什么是\"德莫伊夫雷的定理\"?",
  "De Moivre's Theorem states that raising a complex number in polar form to the nth power gives r^n(cos nθ + i sin nθ). It greatly simplifies computing powers and roots.": "Deivre的Theorem 指出, 以极化形式将复数增加到 nth 电源可以提供 rn( cos n + i sin n) 。 它大大简化了计算能力和根基 。",
  "A signal processing engineer multiplies two impedances: Z₁ = 3(cos 60° + i sin 60°) and Z₂ = 4(cos 30° + i sin 30°). What is the resulting impedance in polar form?": "信号处理工程师乘以两个障碍:Z1 = 3(cos 60° + i sin 60°)和Z2 = 4(cos 30° + i spin 30°)。",
  "Multiply moduli: 3 · 4 = 12. Add arguments: 60° + 30° = 90°. Result: 12(cos 90° + i sin 90°) = 12i.": "乘数模量: 3 □ 4 = 12. 添加参数: 60° + 30° = 90°. 结果: 12(cos 90° + i sin 90°) = 12i。",
  "A physicist uses De Moivre's Theorem to compute (1 + i)⁶. First, 1 + i in polar form is √2 cis 45°. What is the result?": "物理学家使用De Moivre的理论来计算(1 + i) 6. 首先, 极形 1 + i 是 2 cis 45°。 结果是什么 ?",
